question.text: The physical quantity which has the dimensional formula <math><mo>[</mo><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">M</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">T</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>]</mo></math> is

solution.text: <math><mfenced close="]" open="[" separators="|"><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">M</mi><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">T</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>[</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">M</mi><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">L</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">T</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>]</mo></mrow><mrow><mfenced close="]" open="[" separators="|"><mrow><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">L</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>[</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">T</mi><mo>]</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo></math><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfrac><mi>energy</mi><mrow><mi>area</mi><mo>×</mo><mi>time</mi><mo> </mo></mrow></mfrac></math>= dimensions of the solar constant.
